author: Slidebean
description:
Billions of VC dollars are pouring into humanoid robot startups like Figure and Tesla’s Optimus but experts warn the tech is still far from real world deployment.

Famed roboticist Rodney Brooks (iRobot) argues that humanoids still lack true dexterity and fine motor skills that make human movement possible. Others, including Nvidia’s AI research leaders, agree: scaling humanoids could take a decade or more.

👉Hear the full breakdown on: https://vist.ly/4b4sv
title: The world just isn’t ready for humanoids yet

title: Tech Billionaires Are Doom Prepping
